    "Otherwise, the training instance increases the value by one (z i ∈ Neigh(x te D) and y i = y te).",
    "Assuming the training instances are sorted by increasing distance from x te (i.e., x 1 is closest to x te and x n is furthest), then z i 's pointwise kNN Shapley influence is Observe that I kNN-SV 's closed form is linear in n and requires no retraining at all.",
